import urllib.request
import json

# JPMorgan Chase & Co CIK is 19617
cik_padded = "0000019617"

req = urllib.request.Request(
    f"https://data.sec.gov/submissions/CIK{cik_padded}.json",
    headers={"User-Agent": "ResearchBot contact@example.com", "Accept": "application/json"}
)
with urllib.request.urlopen(req) as resp:
    data = json.loads(resp.read())

company_name = data['name']
cik = data['cik']

accessions = data['filings']['recent']['accessionNumber']
dates = data['filings']['recent']['filingDate']
forms = data['filings']['recent']['form']

print(f"Company: {company_name}")
print(f"CIK: {cik}")

# Search for target accession number
target = "0001628280-26-008131"
try:
    idx = accessions.index(target)
    filing_date = dates[idx]
    form_type = forms[idx]
    print(f"Found filing at index {idx}")
    print(f"Filing Date: {filing_date}")
    print(f"Form Type: {form_type}")
except ValueError:
    print(f"Target accession {target} not found in recent filings")
    # Show most recent 10-K filings
    for i, (acc, date, form) in enumerate(zip(accessions, dates, forms)):
        if form == '10-K':
            print(f"10-K found: {acc}, {date}")
            if i > 5:
                break
